President Donald J. Trump has issued a proclamation declaring October 11, 2020, as General Pulaski Memorial Day. General Pulaski, a Polish military leader, fought alongside the Continental Army during the American Revolution. He played a crucial role in the fight for American independence, distinguishing himself as a military leader of great valor and tactical brilliance. General Pulaski was mortally wounded during the Battle of Savannah in 1779. President Trump's proclamation recognizes General Pulaski's ultimate sacrifice and honors the enduring bond between the United States and Poland. It encourages all Americans to commemorate those who have contributed to the nation's progress.